caption: We had such a good experience at North Italia in Washington DC. My toddler and I were planning on picking up our order and picnicking outside but the temperature dropped and got a little too dark. The staff accommodated us not only with no judgment on our not-so-dinner-ready attire but also swiftly gave us a nice table and our food just minutes after. We were able to enjoy the amazing chicken parmigiana and their delicious pizza and since we were now eating in, we ordered dessert. They even provided warm milk for my little one upon request in a perfect sized espresso cup!  She was delighted, and so was I. We both loved the sugared donuts and I got to enjoy my cappuccino. Every single person who we came in contact with was pleasant, friendly and kind. The atmosphere was so welcoming and as a tired Mom with a hungry toddler it was perfectly unexpected and felt special. If you’re looking for a delightful restaurant and delicious Italian in Washington DC, this is your spot. Thank you to everyone at North Italia, we plan to be back ASAP!

OVERALL I ENJOYED MY TIME HERE. THERE WAS A MISHAP WITH BOTH ME AND MY DAUGHTER'S MEALS HOWEVER, THE MANAGER CAME OVER TO MAKE IT RIGHT AND RIGHT AWAY. THE BRAISED SHORT RIB WAS MY FAVORITE. GREAT FOOD, GOOD LAUGHTER AND A NIGHT DEFINITELY WORTH REMEMBERING.

Very mixed feelings about this place unfortunately. My initial impressions were great. Lovely restaurant, beautifully decorated, very clean, and super friendly hostess greeting people at the door. Unfortunately things went downhill.  Our server, while polite and professional, was not very outgoing or friendly. I'm assuming someone was training with him that day because he had another server following him around, but I found it odd that he didn't tell us this since normally that's what I've seen.  I was in a party of two and we each ordered a drink and appetizer to start when we arrived at 6pm. The restaurant had maybe 5 other tables there and it took us almost 15 minutes to get our drinks. We then ordered our main meals. At 6:45pm (45 minutes after being seated) we finally got our appetizers. The servers basically disappeared during this waiting time, and only came by once about 20 minutes in to let us know the appetizers were almost ready. We also had to ask for clean plates since our bread plates were dirty. It took 2 tries to get plates that were totally clean.  The truffle bread appetizer was absolutely delicious! Unfortunately the avocado salad had avocado that was very brown. Our main meals arrived about an hour after sitting down (7pm). I had the squid ink pasta for my main meal, and while the pasta was very good, the shrimp were super overcooked and tough. My friend had the chicken pasta which he enjoyed a lot.  I wanted to try dessert, but was afraid it would take too long. We asked for our check which came quickly, but after providing our credit cards it took almost 10 minutes to get them back.  Mostly my complaints are about the long delay. For a simple meal with two people and a fairly empty restaurant, it took us 1 hour and 40 minutes to have dinner. I would have been okay with this if someone had explained the delay to us, but we were treated as if it was normal. I wasn't super upset with the food quality, and overall it was acceptable and still tasty.

I can see why this place gets only 3.5 stars - subpar hit/miss dishes with a hefty price tag. The Burrata Tortellini and Hazelnut Torta, and Sangria were the stand-outs of the night while the White Truffle Garlic Bread, Margherita Pizza, Apple Bourbon missed the mark.  Apple Sour Bourbon (2/5) - The heap of ice really diluted from the flavor. Couldn't taste the Apple-soaked Bourbon or the spices in the drink. After a few sips, the $12 cocktail was quickly depleted. Definitely get the sangria over the bourbon - tastier and cheaper!  Red Sangria (5/5) - Fruity and perfect blend of brandy, red wine, blood orange, and strawberries. Not a big fan of sangria at restaurants, but this one was fruity and not sugary. Skip the pricey cocktails and go straight for the sangria!  White Truffle Garlic Bread (2/5) - While it's served in a pipping hot skillet cooked in the gas-fired pizza oven, the grilled bread was smothered in greasy olive oil. Where was the white truffle? Kept searching for it in every bite and finally gave up. While the heap of housemade ricotta and parsley garnish were tasty, they couldn't balance out the olive oil.  Margherita Pizza (1/5) - Watching the pizza cook in a nice flame with a soft pillowy crust, the Neapolitan pizza looked so promising, but sadly a disappointment! The impostor pizza was coated in cheap mozzarella cheese and undercooked. For $15.50, I was expecting dollops of fresh buffalo mozzarella cheese. Best part? The crispy garlicky pillowy crust.  Burrata Tortellini (4/5) - Hands-down the stand-out entree of the night! The creamy burrata cooked al dente was divine! Tortellini is among the most difficult pastas to cook (I can never get it right!). The tomato sugo sauce was a bit too runny as the pasta didn't absorb the sauce. Sadly, I couldn't enjoy them together, a thicker chunkier sauce would do the trick.  The Hazenut Torta (5/5) - Saving the best for last! The decadent chocolate torta sitting on a bed of nutella sauce with crunchy hazelnut toffee pieces atop creamy salted gelato melting down was the perfect sweet ending to our meal. Although we didn't have room for dessert, glad we still went for it!  After dropping $250 on 7 dishes (Prosciutto Buschetta, Chicken Parm, and Filet Mignon), we were stuffed - but not truly satisfied.  Get pretty packed on Sat nights, luckily there were a small table open for the 3 of us for a walk-in. If you have a larger group, definitely make a reservation.  Would be back for happy hour on the weekdays for $5 sangria and bruschetta. I prefer Flower Child next door - tastier food that's also more affordable. A better bang for your buck!
Phenomenal service, food, and place. The service is great and the food is just as good. The place is very clean, as well as having a very modern feel.
Very impressed with the experience here.  Every food dish we tried was great: truffle garlic bread, calamari, waygu skirt steak, burrata torteloni, and cocktails.  Will definitely be back.

(Translated by Google) I took a delicious daiquiri accompanied by various snacks ... Cozy and beautiful atmosphere. Directly across from IFC offices. Worth to enjoy the happy hour !!!  (Original) Tomei um delicioso daiquiri acompanhado por petiscos diversos... Ambiente acolhedor e bonito. Bem em frente aos escritórios do IFC. Vale à pena aproveitar a happy hour!!!
Amazing food, friendly staff definitely recommend if your looking for restaurant in D.C.

Had high hopes for this place as new go-to but was underwhelmed by the service. We were seated and waited 10 minutes for a server to take our drink order. Zucca fries were recommended and they were under seasoned and just tasted oily so we stopped eating them. We got our entrees— the chicken parm was well seasoned and rigatoni was good. We asked for a dessert menu and were given our check instead. Felt very rushed and ignored.

Went here for dinner last night and it was delicious! The atmosphere is very welcoming and relaxing, and the service is spot-on! We had the Burrata for an appetizer and the Bianca pizza (highly recommend both, the lemon oil on the Bianca makes the meal!) We were treated very well by the server and manager and prices were very reasonable for a nice restaurant in DC!
Delicious
I had the squid ink pasta with seafood the food was good. Though I thought the portion size for the price $22 (lunch) was too high.
Wow just wow, this place was perfect for a hungry group
Amazing place, friendly staff, and the brunch is beyond phenomenal!
Amazing brunch... For someone who loves italian/french cooking... This is the spot... We had our brunch @12:30... still great... you always can create your own
Very modern and fun atmosphere. Delicious and flavorful food. Absolutely would recommend.
North Italia-DC ~ Great lunch with colleagues! Kale salad was very good!!
I had the salmon entree on the lunch menu and it was delicious! Waitress was a bubbly, helpful addition to a fresh, clean ambiance. Will recommend

Really happy to find North Italia here in DC. Last year I went 3 times to California and the best place to eat there was North Italia. Their best plate is the burrata tortellini and the best desert is the hazelnut torta.
Amazing restaurant! Food was fantastic. Service was superb. Carlos was amazing. We would go back any day!
Food wasn't good and it was too expensive

Great looking restaurant. Friendly staff and a really great bartender who knows her stuff. The food is pretty good; tasty and satisfying. The portions are good. The prices are the same as other Italian restaurants in the area.
Excellent 'Strozzapreti'! Wonderful atmosphere and staff were more than courteous. Definitely a place I will visit again and again...

An absolutely life changing experience. The food was amazing. Portions were spot on and the flavor combinations have truly been created by a culinary genius. The ambiance is welcoming with a clean and free flowing vibe. I live in Ashburn, VA and the 45 minute drive was worth EVERYTHING and more. 10/10 stars! highly recommend to anyone that loves a fun food experience.

Love Italian food, especially Maggiano's (since I only live a couple of miles from one), so thought I would give this a try.  I love it even better than Maggiano's.  Ate there at lunch and had the Strozzapreti.  Totally awesome!  Took a friend this evening and had the Short Rib Radiatori while my friend at the spaghetti and meatballs.  Both were excellent as was our waitress, Marcy.  Will definitely be going back and VERY soon!

Absolutely incredible food and service at a very reasonable price for the area. I LOVE Italian food and had the best plate of pasta (the chicken pesto) I have had in a long time! Great vibe, excellent service, great diverse menu, and our server Gabriella was FANTASTIC. My friends and I will definitely be making this one of my regular places!
Garlic truffle bread is immaculate!
Just perfect...food is delicious and visually appealing. Staff is polite and well trained. Id recommend to anyone and def will be coming back soon
The pre-grand opening was wonderful. The food was delicious. #PartywithNorthItalia
